==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Petulant
<hw>Pet"u*lant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>petulans</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>, prop., making slight attacks
upon, from a lost dim. of <ets>petere</ets> to fall upon, to attack: cf.
F. <ets>p⟦eacute⟧tulant</ets>. See <er>Petition</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Forward; pert; insolent; wanton.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Burton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Capriciously fretful; characterized by ill-natured
freakishness; irritable.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Petulant</xex> moods.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Irritable; ill-humored; peevish; cross; fretful;
querulous.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Petulantly</ent>⟦br⟧
